(1, 'SUGAR', 'photo_upload__1509644848_1509644848.png', 'photo_2_upload__1509644848_1509644848.png', '<p><span style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);">The CT International Cotton Exporter is one of the leading exporters of Raw Cotton from India. CT International The Group maintains a loyal customer base by having a strong and long-term relationship with the suppliers and buyers, who are the key drivers for business growth. With its wide network, it conducts&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);"><span style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);">business in all major cotton producing areas of India such as Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra, Gujarat, Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, and Punjab. The CT International mainly exports cotton to countries like China, Vietnam, Indonesia, Pakistan, Thailand, Taiwan, Bangladesh &amp; other importing countries.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);"><span style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);">The CT International offers a wide range of quality products such as Shankar 6, MCU5, Mech1, J34 and many more to cater to the needs of its global buyers. Apart from Indian cotton, it also engages in exporting African, Australia and Brazilian&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);"><span style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);">cotton. With a committed team, the CT International handles the entire stage of cotton exportation, right from sourcing of the cotton to delivering the ready material to the final destination of the buyer. To ensure world-class quality, the CT International has a team of its own experienced quality classers who follow a strict 2-tier quality testing. In the first stage, the Group’s own quality classers pass the cotton at the ginning factories. For the final stage, independent international surveyors are appointed at the port to check the quality of the material at the port warehouse. All the testing takes place at the HVI Lab to guarantee superior quality standards.</span><br></p>', '2017-11-02', 1),
(2, 'WHEAT', 'photo_upload__1509644984_1509644984.png', 'photo_2_upload__1509644984_1509644984.png', '<table width="102%" border="0" align="left" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(244, 244, 242); color: rgb(68, 68, 68);"><tbody style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14.4px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><tr style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14.4px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><td height="20" class="menu_text2" style="padding: 1px; margin: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: center bottom transparent; text-align: justify; color: rgb(89, 57, 55);">Wheat of Grade II and III to be used in food purpose (mainly for flour-milling and baking industry).<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;">Feed wheat to be used in feed purposes and production of animal mixed fodder.<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;">As per customer''s requirement other non-class-generating quality parameters can be analyzed in accordance with internationally recognized and approved methods.</td><td height="20" class="menu_text3" style="padding: 1px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(61, 42, 19); text-align: center;"></td></tr><tr style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14.4px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><td height="20" class="menu_text2" style="padding: 1px; margin: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: center bottom transparent; text-align: justify; color: rgb(89, 57, 55);">Canada and Ukraine is the largest &nbsp;producer of high-quality milling wheat’s in the world, the bulk of which is exported. Originating, positioning, shipping and exporting high quality, and accordingly, premium price wheat’s, in an international trade dominated ‘run of the mill’ low quality, cheaper wheat’s is no easy task.<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;">CT International specialty and activities are centered within the two major types of wheat produced – Canadian spring and winter milling bread wheat’s, and in Durum wheat, used in the manufacture of pasta products. The two major wheat types are each sub-divided into several different grades and classes, with specific quality and milling factors – test weight, protein, Hag berg, gluten content etc. Canadian wheat is often used by the milling industry in a blend with other origin, lower quality wheat’s, which provides a very uniform, consistent strength, and quality of flour produced.<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;"><img src="http://www.ctinternational.co.uk/agricultural_commodities_and_others/images/product_expertise.png" width="249" height="155" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; float: none; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 12px;">CT International product expertise extends to the promotion and development of the use of Canadian AND UKRAINE wheat in the buyers’ palette, allowing the miller to not only improve the overall quality of his flour and semolina, but to do so with a more economical